Text: |also I was the point person on my company's transition from the KL-5 to GR-6 system.|
|So let's talk a little bit about your duties.|
|Now you'll be heading a whole division, so you'll have a lot of duties.|
|But there'll be perhaps 30 people under you so you can dump a certain amount on them.|
|All right then, we'll have a definite answer for you on Monday, but I think I can say with some confidence, you'll fit in well here.|
|But then who? The waitress I went out with last month?|
|No-no-no-no, no! Who, who were you talking about?|
|No, I-I-I-I don't, I actually don't know|
|Hey-hey-hey. You wanna hear something that sucks.|
|Chris says they're closing down the bar.|
|Yeah, apparently they're turning it into some kinda coffee place.|
|Just coffee! Where are we gonna hang out now?|
|Oh my God, oh my God! Poor Monica!|
|He was with her when he wrote this poem.|
|Look, 'My vessel so empty with nothing inside.|
|Now that I've touched you, you seem emptier still.'|
|He thinks Monica is empty, she is the empty vase!|
|Oh, totally. Oh, God, oh, she seemed so happy too.|
|Ah y'know, this building is on my paper route so I...|
|Oh well, the woman I interviewed with was pretty tough, but y'know thank God Mark coached me, because once I started talking about the fall line, she got all happy and wouldn't shut up.|
|Listen, I'm ah, I'm sorry I've been so crazy and jealous and, it's just that I like you a lot, so...|
|Good job Joe! Well done! Top notch!|
|You liked it? You really liked it?|
|I love the specifics, the specifics were the best part!|
|Hey, what about the scene with the kangaroo? Did-did you like that part?|
|I was surprised to see a kangaroo in a World War I epic.|
|They didn't take any of my suggestions!|
|Okay, look, I think we have to tell Rachel she messed up her dessert.|
|What?! What is with everybody? It's Thanksgiving, not...Truth-Day!|
|Yes, and it is my dying wish to have that ring.|
|See, if I'm not buried with that ring then my spirit is going to wander the nether world for all eternity|
|I don't know. Let me see the ring.|
|Thank you. Thank you. Thank you! And|
|Oh, you know, the usual, teaching aerobics, partying way too much.|
|Oh, and in case you were wondering, those are my legs on the new James Bond poster.|

Text: |Can you hold on a moment? I have another call. I love her.|
|So, are we gonna get together or what?|
|Um, absolutely. Uh, how 'bout tomorrow afternoon? Do you know uh, Central Perk in the Village, say, five-ish?|
|Ok. Ok. Having a phone has finally paid off.|
|Even though you do do a good Bob impression, I'm thinkin' when she sees you tomorow, she's probably gonna realize, "Hey, you're not Bob."|
|I'm hoping that when Bob doesn't show up, she will seek comfort in the open arms of the wry stranger at the next table.|
|Oh my god. You are pure evil.|
|Ok, pure evil , horny and alone . I've done this|
|You wouldn't believe what people put in here!|
|Okay, does this look like a garbage can to you?|
|All right, y'know what? We really are late! Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!!|
|Fine. You'll-you'll watch it on video when we get back.|
|Here you go Phoebe! Here you go Phobo! Phewbedo! Phaybobo.|
|Oh, do you need a hug? You don't have to bring me anything!|
|Hey! So Estelle lined up a bunch of auditions for me tomorrow and I'll have my health insurance back in no time.|
|That's great, but shouldn't you be on the toilet right now?|
|Well, I-I got this blinding pain in my stomach when I was lifting weights before, then I uh passed out and uh, haven't been able to stand up since.|
|But um, I don't think it's anything serious.|
|This sounds like a hernia. You have to--you-you go to the doctor!|
|No way! 'Kay look, if I have to go to the doctor for anything it's gonna be for this thing sticking out of my stomach!|
|Why did I have to start working out again? Damn you 15s!|
|I love your place! Where is this guy from?|
|Uh that's an eighteenth century Indian artifact from Calcutta.|
|Oh wow! So, you're more than just dinosaurs.|
|Well, well to sum up, we're having fun, you look young.|
|But that's not enough. So... So...here's a key to my apartment.|
|You don't think this is too fast.|
|Ross, can I talk to you for a minute?|
|Uh, well... Joey and I broke up.|
|Joey is a great guy, but we're just... so different! I mean, during your speech he kept laughing at homo erectus!|
|Anyway I just, uh, I think it's for the best.|
|There was hum... there was another reason that I thought it was time to end it with Joey.|
|I started to realize that I was having feelings for someone else.|
|Ok Geller. Last day of the conference, you know what happens to the keynote speaker.|
|Oh, professor Clerk we're kind of in the middle of a conversation, here.|
|Yeah, can you guys just throw him in the pool later?|
|Or we could throw you both in|
|Aren't we a little old for this?|
|And most importantly I... you-you will have to catch us first.|
|Oh yeah, now everybody wants to be under this hat!|
|Oh, yeah, Bob said there might be flood damage.|
|Yeah, either that, or he has a really big cat.|
|Okay, see that blind guy right there? I'm gonna bash his head in later.|
|Oh umm, my big scene is coming up. Big scene coming up.|
|If you said, "Big lima bean, bubbling up." Would she understand the difference?|
|Oh boy, I just can't watch. It's too scary!|
|Oh yeah well, you know me, babies, responsibilities, ahhh!!!|
|I'll get it! I will get that!|
|Hey, you wanna get something to eat or uh, do you wanna see how long we can throw this ball back and forth? Huh?|
|Hey Ross, wouldn't it be great if we could go two straight hours without dropping it?!|
|I have to pee. And Rachel's in the bathroom!|
|Man, I didn't think we were gonna make it!|
|Oh, unbelievable! We had the best time!|
|Yay!! Oh so, you're not, you're not mad at us anymore?|
|This is so much better than the first time we went out.|
|That was so awkward, we were really nervous.|
|She loves sandwiches, sports, although she is a Met fan, not much of an issue now but if we were ever to have kids, well that's a|
|Oh my God! Listen to you talkin' about having kids. Oh my Joey. Oh, please don't get married before I do.|
|I cannot sleep in a public place.|
|Would you look at her? She is so peaceful.|
|It's okay, y'know, you just nodded off again.|
|My grandmother has this new boyfriend, and they're both kind of insecure in bed.|
|So they're constantly, like, having to reassure each other that they're having a good time.|
|You have no idea how loud they are!|
|Well, if you want, you can stay with Rachel and me tonight.|
|It's just her water breaking. Calm down, will you?|
|Water breaking, what do you mean? What's that, water breaking?|
|Are you insane? I mean Joey, is going to kill you, he's actually going to kill you dead.|
|Okay! You don't think I thought of that?|
|How can you not know which one?|
|Dark, big hair, with the airplane earrings.|
|You see you can't tell which one is which either, dwha!!|
|I don't know, you thought 'See you Saturday' was funny.|
|Look honey, Mark is in fashion okay, I like having a friend that I can share this stuff with.|
|You guys would never want to go to a lecture with me.|
|Pa-haa!! I would love to go with you.|
|Yeah, hey I-I have clothes, I even pick them out.|
|I mean for, for all you know I could be a fashion..... monger.|
|Okay. Honey, I would love for you to go with me. What?|
|What should I wear, now I'm all nervous.|
| I know, we did it!! Hey, that was incredible, huh?!|
|I know, it was amazing! I mean, we totally nailed it, it was beautiful.|
| Thank you, listen, thanks a lot Tribbiani, . Oh my God, look at the time, I gotta catch the bus to the ball.|
|Unless you wanna practice the Foxtrot again? Or-or the Tango?|
| Ahh, thanks but no. You see I-I think I'm ready to dance with girls.|
| Right. Hey, ahh, you wanna come? Marge has a girlfriend.|
| Yeah, you could dance real good with her, she's the same size as me.|
|Oh God, this is so nerve wracking! How-how do you do this?|
|Well, unfortunately, I don't get many callbacks so|
|Is it a good sign that they asked us to hang around after the audition?|
|Okay uh, we have narrowed it down to Raymond, Ben, Kyle, and Joey. The rest of you, thank you very much.|
|Yes!! I knew it!! Bye-bye! So long! Later!|
|Oh this is great! I might actually get to play Ben's dad!|
|Yeah because you all have such different looks, we're putting you with Raymond and Kyle with Ben.|
|So it'll be either you two or you two.|
|Man, this is gonna be kinda weird.|
|No, we-we're gonna be like best friends, that's why it's gonna be weird.|
|Okay, come on, I can't get married until I get something old, something new, something borrowed, and something blue.|
|Okay, all right, all right, all right! Okay! Okay, here's something, here's something blue and new.|
|I-I hurt three huge men, I gave a guy a bloody nose--I mean I-I'm not proud of it but, I really am.|
|And it's all because of you, wonderful, amazing you.|
